                                                                                                 •    Assurance. Assurance that a cryptographic module is properly and securely implemented
                                                                                                      is essential to the effective use of cryptography. NIST maintains validation programs for
                                                                                                      several of its standards for cryptography (see section 9.2.4). Vendors can have their
                                                                                                      products validated for conformance to the standard through a rigorous set of tests. Such
                                                                                                      testing provides increased assurance that a module meets stated standards, and system
                                                                                                      designers, integrators, and users can have greater confidence that validated products
                                                                                                      conform to accepted standards.
